Dialogue: 0,00:00:59.880,00:01:00.140,辉英,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:00.520,00:01:08.240,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you put this initial condition in the solver we just did, the solution here is going to
Dialogue: 0,00:01:08.240,00:01:09.460,辉英,,0,0,0,,stay stationary.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:10.860,00:01:14.140,辉英,,0,0,0,,D U D T is going to be 0 for a solution like this.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:14.500,00:01:16.000,辉英,,0,0,0,,And why is D U D T equal to 0?
Dialogue: 0,00:01:16.520,00:01:21.300,辉英,,0,0,0,,The only reason D U D T can be 0 is all the F interfaces are the same, right?
Dialogue: 0,00:01:21.840,00:01:25.100,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because D U D T is the difference between two fluxes.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:25.240,00:01:29.140,辉英,,0,0,0,,So if all the flux values are the same, then D U D T is of course 0.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:29.140,00:01:31.720,辉英,,0,0,0,,Why am I claiming f is going to be the same?
Dialogue: 0,00:01:32.140,00:01:34.860,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because, well, other than the two boundary conditions.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:35.360,00:01:37.440,辉英,,0,0,0,,So let's see if we get rid of the boundary conditions.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:37.820,00:01:39.880,辉英,,0,0,0,,So why is f interface the same?
Dialogue: 0,00:01:40.040,00:01:42.740,辉英,,0,0,0,,That is because all the f's are the same.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:43.340,00:01:48.260,辉英,,0,0,0,,All the f's are the same because u is either 1 or minus 1.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:48.760,00:01:54.820,辉英,,0,0,0,,So when you square this solution u, either 1 or minus 1 is going to get you half.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:55.620,00:01:58.300,辉英,,0,0,0,,So all of this vector f is going to be half.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:58.300,00:02:01.020,辉英,,0,0,0,,Therefore, all of this f interface is going to be half.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:01.180,00:02:02.660,辉英,,0,0,0,,Therefore, du dt is going to be 0.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:03.520,00:02:04.060,辉英,,0,0,0,,Any questions?
Dialogue: 0,00:02:06.440,00:02:07.200,辉英,,0,0,0,,No, right?
Dialogue: 0,00:02:07.340,00:02:10.920,辉英,,0,0,0,,So let's say here we don't have a periodic domain.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:11.080,00:02:14.480,辉英,,0,0,0,,So let's, for example, if we have a periodic domain, it goes like that.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:14.520,00:02:17.480,辉英,,0,0,0,,Then the solution is going to stay the same forever, right?
Dialogue: 0,00:02:17.840,00:02:23.520,辉英,,0,0,0,,We have one normal shock over here and one inverted shock over here.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:23.620,00:02:26.920,辉英,,0,0,0,,But the inverted shock should not stay there.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:26.920,00:02:28.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,It should not exist.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:28.300,00:02:36.500,辉英,,0,0,0,,So let me answer the question why it should not exist.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:37.520,00:02:42.560,辉英,,0,0,0,,Why this shock wave should exist and why this shock wave should not exist.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:44.540,00:02:48.560,辉英,,0,0,0,,Mathematically, there is nothing that says this shock wave shouldn't exist, actually.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:49.800,00:02:53.540,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you look at the differential equation, look at, I mean, when shock wave exists,
Dialogue: 0,00:02:53.540,00:02:55.700,辉英,,0,0,0,,you shouldn't look at the differential form of the equation.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:55.800,00:02:58.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,You should look at the integral form, right?
Dialogue: 0,00:02:58.380,00:03:02.880,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you look at the integral form, there is nothing that says that this shock wave shouldn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:03.660,00:03:06.140,辉英,,0,0,0,,A stationary solution is a perfectly valid solution.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:06.920,00:03:11.680,辉英,,0,0,0,,But you will never see that perfectly valid mathematical solution in real world.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:13.500,00:03:24.260,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because the differential equation we are solving is just an approximation of the limit of a viscous process as that viscosity goes to 0.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:25.260,00:03:27.260,辉英,,0,0,0,,Okay, again, it's a limit of...
Dialogue: 0,00:03:28.300,00:03:32.300,辉英,,0,0,0,,A differential equation with very, very small viscosity.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:33.080,00:03:38.540,辉英,,0,0,0,,The Burgess equation we are solving, we actually don't want to solve the Burgess equation.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:38.540,00:03:40.540,辉英,,0,0,0,,So let me just write as f of u.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:40.680,00:03:47.860,辉英,,0,0,0,,We want to solve the Burgess equation with the infinitesimal epsilon times the second derivative of u with respect to x.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:47.860,00:03:49.580,辉英,,0,0,0,,That's a viscous term.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:49.580,00:03:54.120,辉英,,0,0,0,,That's actually why we want numerical viscosity when there is a shock wave, right?
Dialogue: 0,00:03:54.120,00:03:56.880,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is the physical viscosity that is there.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:56.880,00:03:58.260,辉英,,0,0,0,,We're just taking the limit.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:58.260,00:03:59.620,辉英,,0,0,0,,The velocity of epsilon goes to infinity.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:02.300,00:04:11.980,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, if you consider this equation, what is the effect of this epsilon term on the shape of the discontinuities?
Dialogue: 0,00:04:13.780,00:04:17.340,辉英,,0,0,0,,Okay, so if you just think of the heat equation, right?
Dialogue: 0,00:04:17.480,00:04:22.520,辉英,,0,0,0,,So just don't think about the nonlinear term yet.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:22.700,00:04:24.520,辉英,,0,0,0,,Let's just think of the effect of this term.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:24.920,00:04:27.160,辉英,,0,0,0,,What is the effect of this term?
Dialogue: 0,00:04:27.160,00:04:28.160,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's more of a...
Dialogue: 0,00:04:28.260,00:04:32.380,辉英,,0,0,0,,It smoothies out non-smooth features, right?
Dialogue: 0,00:04:32.460,00:04:40.780,辉英,,0,0,0,,So actually near discontinuities, this term is going to be infinitely larger in magnitude than the first-order derivative term.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:42.280,00:04:48.840,辉英,,0,0,0,,So the effect of this is going to make the shock wave not exactly like this, but like that, right?
Dialogue: 0,00:04:48.880,00:04:51.120,辉英,,0,0,0,,So it'll be smoothed out a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:51.340,00:04:54.320,辉英,,0,0,0,,The slope of the shock wave is no longer going to be infinity.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:54.320,00:04:57.320,辉英,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's still going to be 10 to the 18.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:58.260,00:04:59.860,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's still going to be 10 to the 18.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:59.860,00:05:01.580,辉英,,0,0,0,,Maybe the first-order derivative is going to be 10 to the 18 or something.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:01.580,00:05:02.980,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's going to be very, very large.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:03.020,00:05:05.400,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it's not going to be infinity.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:05.400,00:05:17.320,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, if you look at the xt diagram, and zoom into this region where on the left hand side it's minus 1, on the right hand side, let's zoom into this region.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:17.320,00:05:21.680,辉英,,0,0,0,,At the left hand side, the characteristics is minus 1 going this way.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:21.680,00:05:25.260,辉英,,0,0,0,,At the positive side, it's going that way.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:25.260,00:05:27.340,辉英,,0,0,0,,But in the middle, there is a very tiny range.
