Dialogue: 0,00:06:20.920,00:06:26.380,辉英,,0,0,0,,But in between, there is going to be a wider and wider range of solutions that lies in between 0 and 1.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:26.920,00:06:29.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,So this slope is going to be shallower and shallower.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:33.740,00:06:37.400,辉英,,0,0,0,,Numerically, we are not going to capture that with the upwind scheme.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:38.280,00:06:40.040,辉英,,0,0,0,,We just code it up.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:42.040,00:06:46.100,辉英,,0,0,0,,But the fix is not very difficult.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:47.100,00:06:50.360,辉英,,0,0,0,,Do you all understand what the problem is here?
Dialogue: 0,00:06:50.920,00:06:55.860,辉英,,0,0,0,,What is the problem we are dealing with here?
Dialogue: 0,00:06:56.960,00:07:03.320,辉英,,0,0,0,,So the solution to this is to always compute a numerical flux that is physical.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:05.120,00:07:10.660,辉英,,0,0,0,,And by physical here, there is a way to look at the entropy of the solution here.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:11.120,00:07:16.820,辉英,,0,0,0,,So even if you have an infinitesimal amount of viscosity, the entropy should not decrease.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:16.920,00:07:17.700,辉英,,0,0,0,,It should increase.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:17.700,00:07:20.700,辉英,,0,0,0,,Well, if you have a solution that is unique.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:20.920,00:07:24.280,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you have an inverse shock, the entropy actually would decrease.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:24.740,00:07:28.300,辉英,,0,0,0,,So let me say what is the non-physical solution.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:28.640,00:07:32.500,辉英,,0,0,0,,Non-physical solution is you have an inverse shock sitting over here.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:32.660,00:07:36.300,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the characteristics emerges out of the discontinuity.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:37.100,00:07:43.340,辉英,,0,0,0,,So the entropy condition says that whenever you have a discontinuity,
Dialogue: 0,00:07:43.340,00:07:50.720,辉英,,0,0,0,,for example, this one, characteristics can disappear.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:50.920,00:07:56.160,辉英,,0,0,0,,And when things disappear, it's an increase of entropy.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:56.580,00:08:02.980,辉英,,0,0,0,,But you cannot have any new information coming out of nowhere, coming out of a discontinuity, for example.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:03.520,00:08:09.460,辉英,,0,0,0,,So you should not have any new characteristics emerging out of a discontinuity.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:10.640,00:08:15.200,辉英,,0,0,0,,Okay, so things can dissipate, can disappear, but it cannot come out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:16.460,00:08:20.880,辉英,,0,0,0,,So that's the so-called entropy condition we need to satisfy.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:20.920,00:08:25.300,辉英,,0,0,0,,When we are using a numerical method to solve the differential equation.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:27.880,00:08:33.060,辉英,,0,0,0,,Okay, so this is not allowed.
